Instalar Git en la computadora, solo se va a usar el bash.

Crear repositorio en GitHub.

Iniciar sesion en bash, para eso, configuracion de usuario:
git config --global user.name "santiagtms"
git config --global user.email "santiagtms@gmail.com"
git config --global --list
  
Clonar el repositorio en GitHub a repositorio local, para eso:
git clone "URL"

Con el repositorio clonado, los comandos mas comunes son:
git status #this will show you what changes you have done
git add [path/file] #this will prepare that specific file for commit, to add all files at once, use add .
git commit -m "Change description" #this will commit the changes with specific description
git push origin master #this will copy your changes to Github
git pull origin master #Download the latest files from Github
